<DD>The court concludes, on its own motion, that oral argument will not assist the court in this case.&nbsp;  Accordingly, the court will dispose of the petition for review without oral argument on the basis of the record and the presentations in the briefs.&nbsp;  <U>See</U> D.C. C<SMALL>IR.</SMALL> R<SMALL>ULE</SMALL> 34(j).
