<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<h1>Greg Ganske: Surgeon-congressman</h1>

<h3>A gentleman scholar, policy wonk, who's also a regular guy</h3>

<blockquote>
    <p>And for voters who want a congressman with some spunk,
    consider the drug-abuse talk that Ganske gave at a Council
    Bluffs high school.&nbsp; The gist: He used to treat a number
    of young men with enlarged breasts.&nbsp; Why?&nbsp; Because frequent
    use of marijuana has a feminizing hormonal effect.&nbsp; And
    just to be sure, he examined his patients' testicles for
    shrinkage.&nbsp; His message: Don't just say no to drugs, say
    no to embarassing physical changes.</p>
</blockquote>

<p><strong>THIS ARTICLE</strong><em>, written by editorial-page
staff writer Alyssa Haywoode, is one of a series based on
meetings between candidates and The Register's editorial board.</em></p>

<p><em>The Des Moines Register, Friday, October 18, 1996, Page
15A.</em></p>
</body>
